      .u-body-copy
        h3.mt2.u-text-center
          strong
            | Process
        p We began the design process by talking to moms, both those who breastfeed, and those who use formula to learn what kinds of issues they had with breastfeeding in public. We discussed issues they faced when traveling with their children, and worked to develop messaging that would resonate with new moms. We developed an indepth onboaring that welcomed mothers to the platform, introduced them to the Mamava units, and showed them around.
        p As we began testing this onboarding with users, we found that the onboarding was too indepth, and users became frustrated with the number of steps involved. We also discovered much of the interface was intuative and didn't require as much explanation as we had previously thought. We went back to the drawing board and come up with a shorter three-step onboarding that tested better with users.
